Samsung’s incredibly immersive QN90B Neo QLED TV is already a winner in terms of TV viewing. As the global number one TV manufacturer for 16 consecutive years Samsung continues to deliver customer-centric innovation, which powers Samsung screens including immaculate, true-to-life picture quality optimised for a multi-device experience – including gaming. It’s even received a prestigious ‘Gaming TV Performance’ certification from VDE in Germany. Excitingly, the HDR10+ GAMING standard adopted by Samsung’s 2022 Neo QLED line-up empowers users to enjoy cutting-edge visuals, richer and life-like images as well as enhanced control over your preferred settings. As South Africans increasingly begin to view their TVs as gaming devices, they are witnessing first-hand how factors like high image and audio quality as well as low input lag can combine to take their gaming to the next level. These are a few of the reasons why the QN90B Neo QLED TV translates into a super- responsive gaming experience. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-450396 size-full" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Samsung-Gaming-TV.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Samsung-Gaming-TV.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Samsung-Gaming-TV-595x400.png 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Samsung-Gaming-TV-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> You can now forget about game lag, tearing and stuttering with your TV and console teaming up to support your every play. Then, with Certified AMD FreeSync Premium Pro core technology, you can enjoy an awesome combination of smooth gaming, exceptional high dynamic range visuals and low latency. Expect next-level performance for those at the pinnacle of their gaming, a 4K@144Hz refresh rate, AMD FreeSync Premium Pro, and the added convenience of four HDMI 2.1 ports for all of your high-end game devices. Another exciting innovation – with a cloud gaming pad in your hands, you can now control your TV without additional controllers. Starting from 2022, Samsung supports all the latest cloud gamepads and with these controllers, you can control your TV and gain access to gaming Hub. Additionally, on the impressive 2022 Neo QLED TV, Game Bar allows you to monitor gaming status and optimise game settings easily with Game-Iconic UX/UI. It provides key information like input lag, real-time FPS, HDR, VRR, and Bluetooth pairing sound device. A welcome extra- Neo QLED 2022’s new feature, Zoom-in mode will be your wingman that brings victories to your wars. You can choose specific areas you want to see to win the game such as Minimap, Flight information, Status for skill, and Chat area, and enlarge them on the upper part of the screen. The advantages keep coming. The new Ultra wide Multi View will make you a strategist when using the black zone on top of the Super Ultra-wide screen with 32:9 ratio. Of course, you can simultaneously play all apps that Multi View supports. The QLED TV is a game-changer in the true sense with the impressive AI-based surround sound and object tracking sound delivering exactly where you want it most. You can now feel like your gaming station is non-intrusive, ready for action anytime and an essential part of the home’s entertainment set up. When you ready to play the Neo QLED is always ready to work. Click here for more on the incredible QN90B Neo QLED TV and its pricing.